JOHANNESBURG - Business confidence is at its highest in two and a half years, it is now at 99.7 points. Apart from a more improved and positive business mood, short-term economic and market indicators also show an upbeat business climate. In October 2015, the business confidence index measured at a100.2 points and it improved by 3.3 index points in January 2018. READ: Rand stays under pressure as Zuma refuses to go The chamber says the expectation is that new leadership, will lead to more pragmatic and predictable business and economic policy options. Increased trade import volumes, a stronger weighted rand exchange rate and higher retail sales volumes had the most notable positive monthly influence. Expectations are that if current conditions persist, growth for South Africa could well exceed International Monetary Fund forecasts of 0.9 percent growth. eNCA